work.title: Serenata in vano
Serenata in Vano
for klarinet, fagot, horn, cello og kontrabas
for Clarinet, Bassoon, French Horn, Cello and Double Bass

history.p: Nielsen seems to have composed his quintet, Serenata in vano, in May 1914, that is before he began composing his Fourth Symphony (CNW 28) in the summer. The quintet was performed on a concert tour in the provinces by members of The Royal Danish Orchestra, who probably also commissioned the composition.

event.desc: Hornist N. A. Rasmussen fell ill and was replaced by a violist.
